the following technology stack have been implemented or used in the development process:

Python: The core programming language used for developing the backend of the Dairy Farm Management System.

Flask: A micro web framework for Python used for building web APIs and handling HTTP requests.

SQLAlchemy: A Python SQL toolkit and Object-Relational Mapping (ORM) library used for database operations.

MySQL: A popular open-source relational database management system used to store and manage data.

curl: A command-line tool for making HTTP requests, which you've used for testing your API endpoints.

Vagrant: A tool for managing development environments, allowing one to create a consistent and isolated environment for your project.

Virtual Environment (venv): Used to create isolated Python environments for your project, ensuring dependencies are separate from the system-wide Python installation.

Git: Using version control with Git for tracking changes to the codebase.
